SIMPLE: elison
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Elison
<hw>E*li"son</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>elisio</ets>, fr. <ets>elidere</ets>, <ets>elisum</ets>, to strike
out: cf. F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧lision</ets>. See <er>Elide</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Division; separation.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Gram.)</fld> <def>The cutting off or suppression of
a vowel or syllable, for the sake of meter or euphony; esp., in poetry,
the dropping of a final vowel standing before an initial vowel in the
following word, when the two words are drawn together.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Elisor</ent>⟦br⟧
